column5: . From what I have been reading ,if it has the lid,it,s more valuable. It has a few chips,but other then that,it,s in great shape. I just did a spit and shine on it for the mrs,s.  The last going price I seen was 75 bucks. Seems pretty low for a piece of old history.  Hope some one here knows the value these days.  Thanks
Wait til I tell her.  Might hold out for another ten years.  Thanks Terry.
I will expect the going commission  lol
How about the equivalent in peanut butter?
I love peanut butter, so sure
YES HE DOES. I like cold pizza,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,with anchovies. Were fishing after all.LOL
Cool Jar -  fill it up with peanuts, and put  six pack of Stubbies (Labbatt's 50 maybe?) next to it and you got some real nostalgia.
peanut butter is on sale next week at no frills ...yum
Better cash in now while the peanut jar economy is hot. Amazing what some people value.
Planters peanuts are awesome when ice fishing. YUMMMMMMM.
If the internet has taught us anything, asking $75.00 and getting $75.00 for an item is two different things.
Fill it up with loonies and I'll give you $75
